... as an Iksar I had to work hard to get my faction up to Indiff with the Katta guards. Even though the quest giver (Roshawna) is on a different faction (Dah Khura) which is the Vah'Shir shaman faction. Everyone is indiff  on this to start. So with both factions at indiff and all the items collected I was ready to do the quest. <br>
So I stroll into Roshawna's room and before I could say Swiss Family Robinson I have 2 guards, Roshawna and a Barbarian (which I'll come to) knocking the living hell out of me. I precede to run to the exit (as you do) and I'm rooted at the door ...... LOADING PLEASE WAIT ..... hehe nice reflexes Rosh <br>
The Barbarian in the room (Broote &quot;Rat B*****d&quot; Malicus) is on a completely different faction (Concilium Universus). They are spread all over the city and are kinda like the Admin arm of Katta. All evil races will be scowling to this from the get go. But he must also be very closely tied in with Guard and Roshawna's faction, cuz as soon as he attacked me, everything else did.<br>
Anyway ... Concilium Universus faction is extremely hard to get up. I know of 1 quest which raises this faction, using all those Grimling Mining Picks  But you need to be Indiff to do that quest. Saw 1 suggestion on this board which mentioned killing anything on Heart of Seru faction will give CU hits. Now I've ran around Sanctus and it seems one would need 3-4 groups to get deep enough to hit Hearts of Seru.<br>
So for me this is a major stumbling block, and am extremely surprised not to have heard of similar nightmares. The workaround I can think of is charming them, but this could be difficult, as charming 1 would probably agro the other. Oh well I suppose its worth a shot ...<br>
